r doesnt show them and thereby reduces distraction, although bookmarks (and their favicons) are one of the few areas they make sense, since they improve recognition.','2012-02-10T10:05:04.997',1042,NULL),(1975,1086,0,'Id classify this as a `bug`. Might even get the attention of a team member. Shouldnt be too difficult to fix.','2012-02-11T14:11:04.820',1042,NULL),(1976,1093,0,'Yes they do, but unlike the graph view they show multiple days (admittedly sections, but still showing more clutter) and both remove the graph that allows you to easily flick from day to day.','2012-02-11T19:53:34.917',9495,NULL),(1977,1094,0,'Here is an example of such an erroneously signatured comment in action, if you still dont get it.','2012-02-12T01:29:08.693',12285,NULL),(1978,1094,0,'Looks okay to me here. Can you post a screenshot of a bad one? http://i.imgur.com/Zf7Ov.png','2012-02-12T01:34:22.023',2220,NULL),(1979,1094,0,'@NathanGreenstein Yes, its showing up that way for me, now, as well. Unfortunately, the edit link is now remarkably unresponsive...','2012-02-12T01:40:13.157',12285,NULL),(1980,1094,0,'Here is a comment that causes my signature to wrap in the manner I just described.','2012-02-12T01:41:15.183',12285,NULL),(1981,1067,0,'I was wondering if that was normal in terms of the meta membership expressing opinions about the questions asked this way. I wonder if were to interpret it as dis-satisfaction with our collective answers or more directed to the asker.','2012-02-12T02:36:30.480',5472,NULL),(1982,1067,0,'@bmike Hmm, thats a good question. Ive always assumed that people were voting based on whether or not they thought that the question was something that provoked useful feedback from the candidates, but I havent really looked at it in depth before.','2012-02-12T02:41:03.080',3222,NULL),(1983,722,0,'Can this be marked as answered?','2012-02-12T22:59:56.550',12285,NULL),(1984,722,0,'I will review that tomorrow when a blog post goes up.','2012-02-13T00:13:11.687',1346,NULL