2,'Exactly. Questions about pre-release software are almost all too localized, because pre-release software changes so fast and has so many bugs.','2012-02-16T17:04:41.037',2220,NULL),(2013,1115,2,'@GrahamPerrin I would if I could, however mods can only edit the questions section of the FAQ','2012-02-16T17:12:36.413',13,NULL),(2014,1112,0,'Indeed - when faced with that question, the answer at the time was no - SEs not going to integrate things. I could see it needing to be revisited if sites grow enough and site metas never get reputation as a stand alone thing. Perhaps the answer is for sites where the mods want this could lobby for full reputation - same meta handling as MSO.','2012-02-16T19:20:41.283',5472,NULL),(2015,1114,5,'Please reconsider down voting any question if you feel the answer should be no. Instead - up vote the question to acknowledge that the answer is important. Down vote a yes answer and up voting a no answer will let others know the sentiment of the site. By down voting this, you are burying the issue on meta rather than raising it up for all to see...','2012-02-16T19:22:48.550',5472,NULL),(2016,1115,1,'And darn that Apple for releasing a beta version of Messages app on OSX. It isnt going to be localized to less than 6 months of use for the general public given the release schedule as communicated. It also joins Siri as another beta service that is shipping today and users will expect to use and have questions fielded somewhere.','2012-02-16T19:28:54.830',5472,NULL),(2017,1115,4,'@bmike Im on the fence about allowing questions about Messages. Yes, its technically pre-release, but Id argue in name only. The software has been released and is intended for wide adoption.','2012-02-16T19:42:04.000',13,NULL),(2018,1115,7,'I feel strongly that Siri and Messages for OSX should be immediately and explicitly on topic and their tag wikis updated accordingly. See http://meta.apple.stackexchange.com/questions/1119/despite-the-general-rule-to-not-answer-questions-about-beta-products-should-we for consensus building and discussion :-)','2012-02-16T19:44:11.503',5472,NULL),(2019,1119,1,'Great question!','2012-02-16T19:46:01.063',13,NULL),(2020,1120,0,'I like having a place to think these things out so if/when we try it - we can circle back and ensure the goals are met with limited or acceptable downsides over time.','2012-02-16T20:00:09.520',5472,NULL),(2022,1120,3,'I agree. The line could be that this beta is available publicly to anyone (not reserved for developers - and possibly subject to NDA)','2012-02-16T21:38:37.030',90,NULL),(2023,1121,0,'I like this suggestion re: the tags.','2012-02-16T21:52:52.457',1629,NULL),(2024,1121,5,'What if we just mentioned the beta in the tag summary? messages is currently a combined tag for the iOS client and Mac client so marking it all as beta would be bad. I also dont see a need for messages-ios and messages-osx tags until we have a few hundred questions or there is some problem with them together at a later time. Ill think over your suggestion some more...','2012-02-16T21:59:00.860',5472,NULL),(2025,1120,2,'Yes - NDA could be a very, very good defining line. No one is signing a NDA to get these softwares. I would wager anyone with Mountain Lion or beta iOS has verbally (or written/electronically) signed an NDA.(barring theft and intentional or careless breaking of an NDA)','2012-02-16T22:02:14.880',5472,NULL),(2026,1121,1,'+1 for the tags idea','2012-02-16T23:31:48.337',13247,NULL),(2027,1119,0,'Agreed; thanks for clarifying this.','2012-02-17T00:49:39.923',9493,NULL),(2028,1122,5,'I completely agree, except for one thing. I never want to see \"iPod Touch\". (its \"iPod touch\")','2012-02-17T02:20:40.163',13,NULL),(2029,1120,1,'I agree. Public Beta software is fair game. People will be using it, and its disclosed publicly, why shouldnt THE apple stackexchange site field such questions? In Siris case, there are AT LEAST (assuming they use the feature) 4 million users.(see Source link)\n\nWhy should we discount the software considering the probable widespread use, and questions that will come from that?\n\n\n[Source](http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/technology/2011/10/apple-iphone-4s-4-million-sold.html)','2012-02-17T02:45:00.330',2481,NULL),(2030,1122,1,'Related: http://meta.apple.stackexchange.com/questions/444/automatically-capitalizing-ithing-and-ithing-to-ithing','2012-02-17T03:43:32.210',2220,NULL),(2031,1118,5,'This is true, but citing the FAQ on meta is rather backward. The point of the meta discussion is to propose changing the scope of the site, which is then documented in the FAQ. The meta discussion determines what the FAQ should say, not the other way around.','2012-02-17T03:47:14.987',9388,NULL),(2032,1117,1,'This is a false dichotomy. Raising an issue here doesnt preclude reporting it to Apple, and vice versa.','2012-02-17T03:47:55.607',9388,NULL),(2033,1115,0,'I would post a response to the question, except that I agree wholeheartedly with Kyles response here and have nothing to add. Meta is the appropriate place to argue for breaking precedent, but in this case, I believe we are well served by following our general rule that pre-release software is off-topic. In contrast with, say, the example linked in the previous comment.','2012-02-17T03:52:22.250',9388,NULL),(2034,1122,0,'@KyleCronin Ah, youre right; edited.','2012-02-17T04:53:39.083',9493,NULL),(2035,1118,0,'Sorry, I was disoriented. Didnt realise that were in meta!','2012-02-17T09:05:00.880',8546,NULL),(2036,1125,0,'Still, shouldnt it take you to the page which shows you how you earned that rep, i.e. your main site profile reputation page?','2012-02-17T14:08:21.527',12285,NULL),(2037,1125,2,'No, because the meta profile page shows you important details specific to meta. Like your Qs/As and activity specific to meta.','2012-02-17T18:28:13.313',1346,NULL),(2038,1126,0,'Its not [exactly](http://i.stack.imgur.com/fqG1R.png) the same. Close, I agree.','2012-02-19T02:24:51.870