is!','2012-02-28T06:18:59.463',7833,NULL),(2080,1149,0,'Looks great - sounds like you need some Beta Testers tho ;) ;)','2012-02-28T13:03:21.217',9495,NULL),(2081,1149,0,'@GregHewgill Ive been waiting for such a tool for OSX ever since I saw it for Ubuntu! Thank you!','2012-02-28T19:06:41.497',13414,NULL),(2085,1153,4,'Thank you so much for sticking with this! The short answer is were trying to cut down on all CW posts and may want to cull some of the other questions you mention that have all the \"special rules\" needed to explain that they are not just a normal Q&A but instead big lists for voting and discussion.','2012-02-28T19:34:28.810',5472,NULL),(2086,1152,0,'I would encourage everyone that doesnt feel these sort of questions are useful to down vote them. Talking here, discussing all make it easier for the mods to step in and either fix the deficiencies or perhaps close these sort of questions.','2012-02-28T19:35:42.147',5472,NULL),(2087,1151,0,'Huzzah! Voting is _very important_ for showing that a question is contentious. Just because something is popular doesnt mean it should remain.','2012-02-28T19:36:32.270',5472,NULL),(2088,1153,0,'Define \"CW posts\"?','2012-02-28T20:15:56.857',17580,NULL),(2089,1153,0,'CW = Community Wiki, which has generally been used for list-style posts in the past.','2012-02-28T20:19:32.533',9388,NULL),(2090,563,0,'Is there any chance you all will be doing a run for the newly elected moderators on all of the site elections? They sure look snazzy :-)','2012-02-28T20:33:56.957',5472,NULL),(2091,1155,0,'I think thats the point of hardware input devices, they are in some cases around for a longer time than originally intended. That does not reduce there functionality, in fact it sometime might enhance the opportunity for more interesting use cases and or hacking...','2012-02-28T20:36:42.133',17580,NULL),(2092,1152,1,'Also http://meta.apple.stackexchange.com/questions/697/how-to-kill-off-community-wiki-entries makes a good point where n