nternet?','2012-11-30T07:04:50.230',58,NULL),(2832,1504,0,'@Diago fair enough.','2012-11-30T14:12:56.830',9388,NULL),(2833,1508,0,'I am asking people to list what criteria would be used for that one-by-one process. Ill certainly weigh in with an answer - but I didnt want to prime the pump with my views. At present Im just commenting from the point of a moderator. What normal users dont see is the 10 to 30 spam answers, new people saying they want to ask a new question in response to one answer in the large survey. The core problem with the large survey is search ability. When someone comes with a problem in terminal (for instance) - they cant find an answer buried in the \"top terminal tips and tricks\".','2012-11-30T14:40:21.610',5472,NULL),(2834,1509,0,'Now this is what Im talking about - can we generalize some \"rules\" by which closing bad questions could be a group consensus rather than the moderators doing it. Were not against closing things - but when the community takes care of this for us - we can then spend time on the spam and other \"mod-only\" tasks.','2012-11-30T14:41:47.913',5472,NULL),(2835,1509,0,'I love the way you answered this, even if I dont agree with many parts of your answer. Well, I agree that theyre your personal opinions. I just dont share them.','2012-12-01T02:05:39.213',9388,NULL),(2836,1509,0,'preferring Homebrew over Macports really makes the question show as not constructive','2012-12-01T10:09:01.890',237,NULL),(2837,1511,0,'See the fanboism? A downvote within 5 seconds and the fanboy went to downvote the linked question! \"OMG this guy hates Apple!\"','2012-12-01T15:38:28.833',11105,NULL),(2838,1511,0,'Votes on meta are odd. I upvote things I dont agree with since I appreciate the discussion and want everyone to see it. Others downvote things they dont agree with (and I think most long time SO/SE users vote that way) - cest la vie in an open system ...','2012-12-01T15:52:04.717',5472,NULL),(2839,1512,0,'I reread your question as orig