rrent version of the answer to the question updates\" is an awesome answer. If the poster is actually the person who does the work, sure, Id love to see that explicitly stated, but I dont see \"Im going to answer your question here\" as product promotion.','2013-04-02T15:34:17.567',9388,NULL),(3098,23,0,'@LessPop_MoreFizz Actually that only applies to builds that modify protected parts of the OS; if one does a vanilla install it should be legal. *from what Ive read on pro-hackintosh sites granted','2013-04-03T00:46:50.627',44909,NULL),(3100,1315,0,'What do you think of the answer I have just added?','2013-04-03T19:19:36.833',5472,NULL),(3101,1313,0,'Ive listed some questions I want to keep in a separate answer. After discussing things with the other elected moderators, the initial decision was made to separate the site from the developer centric Stack Overflow and well before itunes-connect became a multi billion dollar enterprise. Times change and this is how we work out if and how we will change with the times.','2013-04-03T19:21:33.823',5472,NULL),(3103,1038,1,'Im going to feature this for a week and then see if any objections are aired by Wednesday the 10th of April and then suggest a FAQ change be made at that point to implement this in the absence of any widespread criticism of this proposal.','2013-04-03T19:57:13.473',5472,NULL),(3104,1038,1,'Sounds good; the proposals been floating around for more than a year. Its time for some action.','2013-04-09T12:51:42.137',9388,NULL),(3105,1038,0,'I have edited the FAQ section and would appreciate several eyes to look for typos and or omissions or inclusions that seem too broad or narrow. http://apple.stackexchange.com/posts/5788/revisions','2013-04-10T16:59:42.440',5472,NULL),(3106,5,0,'Ive removed the faq and featured tags as this was useful at the start, but the FAQ is not in production.','2013-04-11T16:36:27.943',5472,NULL),(3107,1656,0,'The reason I think it is a merge is that I dont think I would have given a simple answer on GIMP a year after at least one illustrated one (or else my mind is really going)','2013-04-12T11:04:22.437',237,NULL),(3108,1585,0,'Thank you for the clear adherence to the site promotion policy. We dont get many questions on TeX, but its nice to have more items here to vote on.','2013-04-13T17:06:16.677',5472,NULL),(3109,1657,4,'If someone can be elected moderator, earn 53K reputation on this site, and still need to ask this, our documentation is really a mess! Or maybe this is a leading question to generate a great answer we can point people to :-)','2013-04-15T13:23:41.490',9388,NULL),(3110,1657,1,'Im clearly asking this as a proxy for others (being that goofy guy out there \"leading by example\"), and even though I have some ideas where the line should lie - Im looking to get several voices in fleshing out the details.','2013-04-15T13:32:37.587',5472,NULL),(3111,1658,0,'My initial thoughts are the linked question is perfect for here. Yes, a developer is asking it. Yes, they eventually need to come to grips with what specific architectural choices Apple made and they have made to cause their version of their app to use 36 MB of space. Those detailed questions belong on Stack Overflow since they are not iTunes-Connect service questions. However, all users of iOS will benefit from the asking of what makes an app use up space on iOS. So, I see us steering that question to keep it broadly applicable and help the OP refine the area for a follow-on question on SO.','2013-04-15T13:35:07.847',5472,NULL),(3112,1657,0,'Of course. I didnt read your name when I asked the question, and was just startled to see it was from you.','2013-04-15T13:36:13.970',9388,NULL),(3113,1657,1,'I initially started to write this as a draft FAQ, but were not there yet. Id rather see several edge questions get discussed / dissected here rather than in comment threads on the main site. In time, we can document a Q&A here to be tagged [tag:faq]','2013-04-15T13:38:02.373',5472,NULL),(