ust icon/title or more?','2016-08-28T16:32:00.563',9058,NULL),(6219,2857,0,'I think its really up to what the developer wants to code from what they can scrape. Slack does a nice job of this currently. http://i.stack.imgur.com/GY4jC.png','2016-08-28T16:39:28.023',5472,NULL),(6220,2857,0,'Open Graph tags `og:site_name`, `og:title`, `og:description`, and `og:image` provide all the information that would be needed. The [iTunes Search API](https://affiliate.itunes.apple.com/resources/documentation/itunes-store-web-service-search-api/) could also work. I would suggest keeping the description short (i.e. truncation).','2016-08-29T06:33:56.613',142875,NULL),(6221,2857,0,'Is there any concern over affiliate links being used? Or even replacing/adding one for Stack to be the affiliate? (Id be fine with that.)','2016-08-29T16:02:21.490',19131,NULL),(6222,2857,0,'I believe Stack Exchange already has code to strip out affiliate links. That would be another reason to handle them as opposed to let people post whatever link they craft. Good suggestion, @incumbent','2016-08-29T16:09:13.487',5472,NULL),(6223,2860,0,'Cool! So even the Apple Lisa would be on-topic?','2016-08-31T11:30:29.077',153510,NULL),(6224,2860,0,'@Fiksdal we have apple II questions so no problem with new hardware :)','2016-08-31T11:36:43.860',237,NULL),(6225,2860,0,'@Mark Nice :) And also cool that you consider it new, lol :) (jk, I know you meant old.)','2016-08-31T11:38:22.140',153510,NULL),(6226,2860,0,'I dont think anyones tried to ask about anything older than the Apple I yet - so you should be just fine with something as new as the Lisa hardware system and software. Again - we arent wikipedia for asking to find history - the question should have a practical aspect about how to do something specific.','2016-08-31T11:38:42.873',5472,NULL),(6227,2860,0,'bmike Sure, Im talking about actual technical questions about use, software, etc. Anyway, cool. BTW, why do both you and @Mark refer to the Lisa as \"new\"?','2